quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,49,"And [remember] when We saved you from Pharaoh’s people, who were inflicting dreadful torment upon you: slaughtering your sons and sparing your women. That was a great trial from your Lord.",""
  2,50,"And [remember] when We parted the sea for you and saved you, while We drowned the people of Pharaoh while you were looking on.",""
  2,51,"And [remember] when We appointed for Moses forty nights. Then you took the calf [for worship] in his absence, while you were wrongdoers.",""
  2,52,"Yet We pardoned you after that, so that you may be grateful.",""
  2,53,"And [remember] when We gave Moses the Scripture and the criterion<sup>30</sup>, so that you may be guided.","[30] Differentiating between truth and falsehood. ""The Scripture and the criterion"" refers to the Torah."
  2,54,"And [remember] when Moses said to his people, “O my people, you have wronged yourselves by taking the calf [for worship]. So repent to your Creator and kill yourselves [i.e., the guilty among you]; that is best for you with your Creator.” Then He accepted your repentance, for He is the Accepter of Repentance, the Most Merciful.",""
  2,55,"And [remember] when you said, “O Moses, we will never believe you until we see Allah openly,” so a thunderbolt struck you while you were looking on.",""
  2,56,"Then We raised you back to life after your death, so that you may be grateful.",""
  2,57,"And We shaded you with clouds and sent down to you manna and quails<sup>31</sup>, [saying], “Eat of the good things We have provided for you.” They did not wrong Us, but they wronged themselves.","[31] They both have linguistic roots in Arabic; ""al-mann"" means that which is God-given without effort, while ""al-salwā"" means that in which one finds consolation and comfort."
